articles.description: B.J. Taylor scored 22 points and made a key shot and two free throws with 16 seconds to help Central Florida beat Memphis 68-64 on Sunday.
articles.headline: UCF ends two-game skid beating Memphis 68-64

articles.description: Bakari Evelyn scored 22 points with four 3-pointers, Max Joseph had 10 of his 12 points in the second half and Valparaiso beat short-handed Illinois State 74-58 on Sunday.
articles.headline: Valparaiso beats short-handed Valparaiso 74-58

articles.description: Lucas Siewert scored a career-high 17 points, including a pair of 3-pointers down the stretch, and the Colorado Buffaloes beat the Stanford Cardinal 64-56 Sunday for their third win in a row.
articles.headline: Buffs win third straight as Colorado downs Stanford 64-56

articles.description: Kavion Pippen scored 21 points with eight rebounds and four blocks and Southern Illinois defeated Bradley 74-57 on Sunday to take over sole possession of second place in the Missouri Valley Conference.
articles.headline: Southern Illinois alone in 2nd in MVC after win over Bradley

articles.description: Upset Saturday in the Big 12 saw four of the league's top five teams lose. No. 19 West Virginia must shake the sting of blowing a late six-point lead at home against Oklahoma State.
articles.headline: No. 19 West Virginia looking to bounce back vs. TCU

articles.description: Bearcats senior Kyle Washington drops 17 points and leads Cincinnati to a 76-51 win over SMU, extending Cincy's perfect streak in the American Athletic Conference.
articles.headline: Cincinnati gets road win over SMU

images.caption: Bearcats senior Kyle Washington drops 17 points and leads Cincinnati to a 76-51 win over SMU, extending Cincy's perfect streak in the American Athletic Conference.
images.name: Cincinnati gets road win over SMU

videos.description: After missing North Carolina's first game with a broken hand, Joel Berry II shows he hasn't missed a beat, draining a deep 3-pointer in his first shot attempt since his return.
videos.headline: Berry splashes triple in first shot since injury

videos.description: After a missed Joel Berry II shot, Sterling Manley goes to the offensive glass to grab the miss and get the putback to go.
videos.headline: Tar Heels' Manley crashes boards to clean up miss

videos.description: Bucknell's Stephen Brown drives to the hoop, but gets denied as both Joel Berry II and Luke Maye get a piece of his shot attempt.
videos.headline: Tar Heels protect the rim

videos.description: Nana Foulland gets the ball in the post and goes to work, spinning around a Tar Heels' defender before throwing down a powerful two-handed slam.
videos.headline: Bisons' Foulland spins and scores with emphatic dunk

videos.description: North Carolina's Luke Maye gets a pass at the top of the key and doesn't hesitate to shoot, knocking down a 3-pointer to give the Tar Heels a 32-22 lead.
videos.headline: Maye connects from deep with quick trigger

videos.description: North Carolina's Joel Berry II uses his quick hands to get a steal and then throws a pass backwards over his head to find Theo Pinson for a transition score.
videos.headline: Berry steals and deals to set up Tar Heels bucket

videos.description: The Tar Heels sling the ball around the perimeter, with four players touching the ball in as many seconds to set up an uncontested dunk for Brandon Huffman.
videos.headline: Stellar ball movement leads to easy UNC slam

videos.description: Zach Thomas connects on a deep 3-pointer just inside of the North Carolina logo to cut the Tar Heels lead to five.
videos.headline: Bucknell's Thomas nails deep 3 from logo

videos.description: Following a Bucknell turnover, Theo Pinson scoops the ball and bullies his way to the hoop for a North Carolina basket.
videos.headline: Pinson goes coast-to-coast for Tar Heels score

videos.description: Sterling Manley gets his shot from the post to fall despite being hit and fouled by Bucknell's Nana Foulland.
videos.headline: UNC's Manley gets hoop and harm on turnaround jumper
